value: You do the scholam proud, Lexmate.
Regard the work of my Lexmate!
The Behemoth shames the rest of you.
It seems the Behemoth has learned from me!
Even a Liability is useful once in a while.
I'll grant that was impressive, Liability.
The Liability outperforms the rest of you...
You find yourselves in the shade of the Liability.
You expect praise for doing your job, conscript?
I could almost believe you were a professional, conscript.
The conscript almost looks like a real soldier today...
The Firebrand shames the rest of you!
You're delivering the Judge of Terra's justice, Firebrand!
Up, Lexmate. There is work for us yet.
Come, Lexmate. The war awaits us.
The war is not over, Behemoth.
Now is not the time for sleep, Behemoth.
You! Behemoth! Get up and fight!
Up, fool. The enemy is not defeated.
Come, Behemoth. There are more foes for you to slay.
Up, Liability. We have no time for this.
Liability! Your penance is not yet served.
Up, Liability. Your duty is not done.
On your feet, Liability. We have need of you yet.
Up, Conscript. There is fighting to do.
Rise, Conscript. You are needed in the fight.
Conscript! You are ordered to stand!
Come, Firebrand, the enemy awaits you.
Your fight is not over, Firebrand.
Your service to the Judge of Terra is not over, Firebrand.
Rise and fight in the Judge of Terra's name.
Faith and fury, Firebrand. Rise and fight.
You damned ingrates have woken it!
You must endure a little longer.
[Cough] Air as foul as our foe.
The only solution for that is fire.
Would that we could burn this filth.
Only half-remnants of function are visible.
May the Lex shine in this darkness!
Tread carefully. The dark is treacherous.
Weapons at the ready. Your faith will be tested in fire.
I grow tired of this interminable gloom.
If you have deserted me, I will have you on a charge...
The Lex is my guide... still, I could use a map.
They have abandoned me. Scofflaws and malcontents, every one.
I am alone. This is... suboptimal.
My solitary status is a breach of regulations.
Hello? Where have you scofflaws gone?
The Lex is with me. Regrettably, no one else is.
With the Judge of Terra as my witness, I will yet forge you into an effective combat unit.
A worthy goal. And a necessary one.
It is an arbitrator's duty to stand firm while others cower.
This is a humbled and benighted world, but we shall restore the sanctity of the Lex Imperialis.
Unity. Discipline. Faith. These virtues are the foundations of victory.
I could not have put it better.
A thoroughfare may be empty, but we are never alone. The enemy gathers in the shadows.
Tertium is corrupt from its deepest roots to its highest pinnacle. But it will not be so forever.
We may not have chosen one another's company, but duty binds us.
Lexbreaking is rife on Atoma. Its extermination is a labour fit to fill a lifetime.
A lifetime well spent, by any measure.
However you began this life, now you are deputies united in upholding the Lex Imperialis.
I shall endeavour to teach you proper protocol. You are sure to find it ... instructive.
The Judge of Terra calls you to serve without fear.
I should not be bonded to such reprobates as those who serve Inquisitor Grendyl.
Strike with precision. With certainty. Let none stand in our way.
To my side, reprobates. Duty calls.
These are dark days. We may not witness their end in our lifetime.
Then we will pass the duty on to those who follow. And they to their inheritors until the work is done.
If I issue an order, it is to be obeyed. Do you understand?
We are all insignificant beside the glory of the Lex Imperialis.
Remember always that the Judge of Terra values your efforts.
And we must ever strive to be worthy of his trust.
Determination and a steeled heart make all things possible.
That is not our concern. Our orders are clear.
I have. I harbour dark suspicions as to the cause.
A generous attitude, partner. Let us hope it does not play you false.
You are too free with your discretion. It will lead you into ruin.
A sour attitude will not aid in our task's completion.
We shall do as the Lex Imperialis decrees. No more, no less.
It must be restored to order, partner. There is much overlap, but it is not the same.
Your Book of Judgement has bloody pages indeed, partner.
A task fit to fill a lifetime with purpose.
That may be true, but we must temper haste with diligence.
We shall defend it to our last drop of blood.
You are a blunt implement, but this world yearns for the strike of the hammer.
Save for disappointing the Judge on Terra, of course.
Such is the fate of those charged with upholding the Lex Imperialis.
Have no fear, Behemoth. I have known darker days than this.
Sanction all lexbreakers as you judge proper, Behemoth. Leave the details to me.
A commendable attitude. Others could learn from it.
You will have opportunities uncounted, be sure of that.
Their first folly was to challenge the Lex Imperialis.
Fun? This is duty, Behemoth. Be glad of it.
Should the Imperium arrange itself according to your pleasures? My judgement is otherwise.
And you do so with ... notable results.
More will come. Upholding the Lex is a battle never-ending.
Then keep your distance! I have no desire to share your outpourings.
Marching builds discipline. Discipline is the root of order.
Hold to your duty, Behemoth, and I shall ensure that your thirst is slaked.
Those and the firm, guiding hand of the Lex Imperialis.
And remember almost nothing, I'll warrant.
Our station is assigned by worth and deed, Behemoth. Those who dwell in such places belong here.
Indeed. A great many things could happen to one with your attitude.
The price paid for heresy and ill-kept lex. We are all complicit.
Your comfort is of no concern.
Then I suspect you will be more happy than sad for the remainder of your brief life.
And I weary of your complaints.
Do not think to issue instruction to me, lexbreaker.
It lacks the order of a guiding hand. As do you.
Much is astray on this world. Resolve and punitive action shall set it right.
You are testing my patience. It is a trial I am likely to fail.
We have all slept too long. This world must be roused to witness the light of Terra once more.
Then your task is both solace and reward.
You will not lack for opportunity. The battle to enforce the Lex Imperialis is never-ending.
Indeed. But familiarity risks corruption. Austere distance is a virtue to those who would bring order.
We are here to stand witness to a lex restored. All else is a distraction.
The law you speak of is but a pale shadow of that which governs the Imperium entire.
Only a narrow mind would think to excuse it so.
Lexbreakers. Or those soon to become so.
I concur. Laxity and sloth are failings we cannot tolerate.
Better still to aspire to serve the Lex Imperialis. There is no higher calling.
You fought your war with thousands of comrades at your side. Too often, an arbitrator stands alone.
I swear by the Throne that I would never shoot you inadvertently.
I am not convinced that you comprehend the meaning of the word "glorious".
Appetite for justice should never flag.
Malcador's Bones! You are a most wretched reprobate.
It is merely another place that clamours for justice.
Indeed. Directness is prefered in all things. Battle most especially.
Fear not the foe. We fight for a higher cause.
Then make it count. Serve to your last breath. Fight until your strength finally ebbs.
If I cannot live to witness my labours completed, death in service is the highest calling.
I concur. Lexbreakers and heretics muster close by.
Hold on to discipline. It is the wellspring of victory.
A veritous decree. The price of lax vigilance.
May our deeds be witnessed and judged worthy.
And from his Lex Imperialis, without which the Imperium would crumble.
I prefer to cleave to precision, duty and vigilance.
But action requires thought, does it not?
Such is the natural order that binds both innocence and guilt to proof.
I am gratified to have attracted his rigour.
And the highest calling, save for the lex.
May it guide us to victory and salvation.
Fear cares not who it serves. It is ours to wield also.
That is not yet proven ... though I expect that you are correct.
Or through the laxness of so-called allies.
Walk wherever you desire, but do not think to issue orders.
What comfort I need, I draw from the Lex Imperialis and the anticipation of its restoration.
How have you never heard the term before,  Behemoth?
You are different. Inferior. But not without purpose.
I will shoot as I see fit!
Your words are nothing but a distraction.
You have been profligate. This is the price.
Did you hit a single target? What a waste.
Ammunition should be in the hands of the deserving. Me.
Mood and disposion are irrelevent, Firebrand. Do your duty.
Irrelevent. Focus on the task at hand.
On this occasion, Liability, I am inclined to heed your words.
Whatever comes, we will face it in the name of the Lex.
Think of the damage a clever ogryn could do ...
Indeed. Let us seek out a new battle.
Gather your strength, Behemoth. The enemy will come.
Your hide is indubitably thick, Behemoth.
An neglected wound will fester. See to your injuries.
Overconfidence will be your undoing, Behemoth.
Do not speak of victory until the final blow is struck.
Up close and personal, yes? I can see the appeal.
Did you ever consider a career in Lex-enforcement?
Enough. You may freeze for all I care.
There remains ample room for improvement.
Continue this way, and you may yet reach competence before you die.
You will not earn my favour with such wheedling words.
What would you know of such matters, Liability?
You are not authorised to die on duty, Conscript.
The Judge of Terra retires us when he will. Keep fighting until then.
You seek to unsettle me, witch? You will fail ... Although I insist you stop trying.
In fact I note from my reports that you've mentioned him on a daily basis.
A notable examplar of service, Behemoth.
Your work is irrelevant. There is only the Lex Imperialis.
We labour for the Judge of Terra, Firebrand.
Try, and I will shoot you where you stand.
Desertion is a capital crime under the Lex.
This is our duty, and our penance.
You insult Atoma's defenders with your words.
I will fight like an officer of the Lex, Conscript.
I need no direction from you, Conscript.
Funny. I've seen a few witches explode in my time...
Volatile, tempermental and dangerous. Remind you of anyone?
Heed the Conscript. We win, or we fail all.
The duty of the Arbitrator is to walk where others fear to tread.
Such fabrications are a violation of Ordinance 267. Desist immediately.
If you have time to dream, you are not fighting hard enough.
I have noted your intent to break intoxicant prohibitions.
All intoxicants will be confiscated. For investigative purposes...
For Him, we uphold the eternal Lex Imperialis!
You should trust in the Judge of Terra. Or else I will make you.
Your attack on morale will be noted in my report.
When the Lex is abandoned, heresy is the only reward.
Your poisonous rhetoric will be noted in my report.
Were the war to end, what purpose would we have?
I do not fear death in the service of the Lex.
Save your breath for the fight.
Fire is only one tool amongst many.
I would recommend you remember, and with haste.
You need not think. Only OBEY.
Concern yourself with the battle at hand.
Silence. Your words are an affront to morale.
I value your praise as little as your contempt.
Perhaps one day you will earn my respect in turn.
Is there nothing you will not eat?
And more to come. Kill them.
Was that medicae for you to waste? I think not.
Hoarding supplies is an offence under the Lex.
I will act as I see fit.
This is your home now.  Fight for it.
Take courage. Or at least grieve in silence.
Not until the Lex is restored here.
Rest while you can. The fight will come.
Patience, Firebrand. The war is not over.
Had Atoma produced better music I might be interested in her culture.
It is only by the Judge of Terra's grace that you remain real at all.
Such peculiarities of perception will be noted in my report.
An appropriate entertainment for the citizenry.
I once played a saint at a scholam drama. Quite definitive, I'm told.
You are a valuable and dangerous resource. Nothing more.
We are burdened with your danger. Don't add whining.
It is for the Judge of Terra to decide how this will end.
We fight for her justice still.
If the time comes to demolish Atoma, perhaps.
I'll consider an upgrade... When I wish the city to collapse around us.
There is no space for such inefficiency.
Your use lies not in strategy, Behemoth.
I ask only to see the Lex restored.
Righteous deeds are prayer enough for now.
The time for thanksgiving will come. Now is the time for duty.
Judge of Terra, grant me strength.
I pray that I may live to see the Lex restored here.
Strength alone cannot win this war.
My mind is a bulwark. Impervious.
I do. I envy you sometimes.
We will rebuild it in the Lex.
The Lex will see it restored to order.
You will have your leave. When you have earned it.
The Lex never rests. Neither shall we.
One day Tertium will ring with song again.
Judge of Terra, grant me strength...
They will be punished all the same.
By the Lex, I will see them brought to judgement.
Forward, in the name of the Lex!
The righteous have no need to hide.
I have no time for your folly.
The stench of criminality. [sniffing] Which of you is it?
I need no cybermastiff to know its source.
Only the Lex can restore it to greatness.
Yet so much has been lost...
A functional team requires a strong leader: Me.
We are ... colleagues at best. Not friends.
Those who abandon the Lex abandon humanity.
The old song. [Snort] I have heard it many times.
When we are finished here, I will request a retrial.
Think, before you mark yourself as a criminal.
Try it and I will have you in chains.
I trust in the Lex and the Judge of Terra.
You may all trust in me.
Speak your accusation plainly, Conscript. I am no traitor.
Your opinion is of no significance.
I WILL see order restored to this place.
You are mistaken. Proper maintenence is the mark of a professional.
All are guilty unless the Judge of Terra deems it otherwise.
The Judge of Terra sees every infraction of the Lex. Mark it.
We enforce the Lex Imperialis for His glory!
We are the Judge of Terra's fists!
Pain is a reminder of duty. Use it.
Does your courage fail you? The battle is here.
Is it your sight that fails you or your wits? The fight is here!
Malcador's bones! The fight is here.
I have need of your weapon here.
In the name of the Lex,return to the fight!
Laugh while you can, abomination. You will perish... eventually.
It is vulnerable to the rear!
No rest until the beast is slain!
What could be fouler than an Ogryn? THIS.
This Plague Ogryn is an atrocity!
Judge of Terra, bear witness to my wounds ...
These wretches have spilled my blood...
By the Lex, a grievous wound ...
I must not perish before my duty is done ...
Pain ... I cannot endure it ... and yet I must ...
Every drop of this blood... I spill gladly...
I cannot fight like this! Aid me!
Aid me! Or face my judgement!
Die, Rager, in the name of the Lex!
Rage will not prevail aginst the Lex!
Another dead Rager! Another victory for the Lex!
A dead Rager. Weak. Repulsive. Corrupt.
Ha. No treats for THIS Hound.
Judge of Terra, that was a challenge.
It didn't stand a chance against the Lex.
Hah! I am the Lex's Hand!
Tox Flamer down. Only the fires of justice remain!
Die, in the name of the Lex!
For the Judge of Terra, finish this!
It will not defeat an Arbitrator!
Vile thing. Death is too good for it.
Filth such as this has no place in the God-Emperor's light.
Hah! That is how you deliver justice!
Ordinance 767 indicates you are due to die.
Prepare to reap the Lexbreaker's reward!
The scan is complete. What now?
We have the data required. What is next?
How many more of these scofflaws can there be?
Their appetite for misrule seems insatiable!
That so many should have fallen into Lexbreaking...
Come, malcontents! I have judgement enough for you all!
This! This is worthy service indeed!
Stand fast! The Judge of Terra is with us!
Ammunition, lexmate! Take it and deliver judgement!
Lexmate! Have you need of ammunition?
Do you see the ammunition, Liability? Take it.
For all your dark power, Liability, you still need ammunition.
Do you not need ammunition, Conscript?
Firebrand! Your prayers for ammunition are granted!
Do you not require ammunition, Firebrand?
Your body is a weapon of the god-emperor, Lexmate. Restore it.
Lexmate! You are wounded! See to the bleeding!
The pain is gone. Yet duty remains.
There. [Sigh of relief]  I may yet live to serve.
Ah ...[Satisfied Sigh] Healing is most welcome.
Judge of Terra, I am fit to serve once more.
Behemoth! Medicae, before your strength fails you!
Heal, Behemoth. We have no need of you dead.
You are wounded, Behemoth -- take this!
A wounded Psyker is a danger to all. Heal.
You! Liability! Heal, before you endanger us all.
Heal yourself, Liability. I have no time to waste on your bleating.
If you would live, Liability, heal yourself.
Your blood belongs inside, Conscript. Heal yourself.
You cannot fight in this state, Firebrand! Heal yourself!
You cannot fight with faith alone, Firebrand! Heal yourself!
Save your wrath for the enemy, Liability.
Strike me again and I will have you flogged, Liability.
Liability! I am not the enemy!
Are you starting a fight, Conscript?
I am not your enemy, Firebrand...
A little less zeal, a little more accuracy, Firebrand...
Violation of district code seven theta five. Disgusting.
Whoever did this should be made to clean it ... With their tongues.
The Lex will show the way!
The Lex shall be our guide!
This way! I am certain of it!
Keep up! I will not slow for you!
It is gratifying to embark on a vital mission.
Finally. An opportunity to deliver justice.
Justice will come to Tertium, delivered by my hand.
Now to deliver the Judge of Terra's justice.
I will ink the Judge of Terra's law in the blood of Lex-breakers.
Heretics, witches, tithebreakers. Prepare for justice.
Just like they taught us at the Scholam.
Remain alert! Majoris Enemy contact imminent.
Time to lay down the Lex!
Stench indicative of a code four-five-nine.
The enemy seeks to ambush us!
A horde comes. Time to fight.
Stand fast. We are a match for even this!
A horde comes. Time to fight.
Fight well, and in the name of the Lex.
Those are their elites. Kill them.
Remain alert, Reprobates. Hounds are damned fast.
They hunt in packs. Prepare to deploy elimination protocols.
So, we will have many targets.
Then we prepare for an onslaught.
Good. But there is more to do!
Ready yourselves, Reprobates. I will not wait for you.
Finally. The Arbitrators would not have kept us so long.

The Lex Imperialis is more than law. It is holy wisdom, handed from the Judge of Terra to those who preserve order. It is not to be questioned or challenged, but enforced unflinchingly and without fear. By bringing the Lex to those that have it not, we bring order to the Imperium, and to the galaxy.
I order you to aid me!
Has my situation escaped your attention?
How much longer must I wait for aid?
What is keeping you from aiding me?
I will see you in chains for this dereliction of duty!
Assist me, immediately, or I shall have you flogged!
You will pay for this negligence, rejects! Assist me now!
Go carefully, lest you crush your fellows!
Try walking with one foot at a time, Behemoth.
Remind me of why you're here again, Liability?
It's strategically apposite to remain upright, Conscript.
A poor performance, even for you, Conscript.
I see you missed basic locomotion training, Conscript.
I command you to help me up! Now!
Give me a hand! That's an order!
I'll report every one of you who doesn't help immediately!
Ah, a grenade. The Judge of Terra's most explosive justice aid.
This healing station is a timely blessing.
Here: a chance to treat our wounds.
A well stocked healing station! God-Emperor be praised!
This is... heavier than it looked.
I presume we are not using the front door?
Not the finest side of Tertium.
We are to pacify and secure? Follow my example ... and my experience.
The inhabitants must scrape an honest living from the filth. Many fail.
This is a place of poverty, but it must still answer to the Lex.
I do not care to be going into combat less than fully informed.
Ah, the heat of righteous industry!
It will be good to taste clean air again. Such as it is.
Sneaking? Do I look like a scofflaw?
Courage is a better weapon than stealth.
We shall rise from this filth and deliver judgement upon the deserving!
The air here tastes like superheated plasteel!
This facility is surely crucial to the war effort. Do you not agree?
Technology is best left to the qualified.
To touch the sacred machine is forbidden.
No vox broadcast can subvert a soul unless it is already wayward.
We are at considerable altitude. It is enough to make my head spin.
I have reviewed our plotted route. It is ... scenic.
The air is strange up here. It lacks the mandated mood-suppressants.
We have walked into a trap!
Vox signal compromised. Do not lose heart!
Vox signal is dead. It may also be our fate.
We should disable those skyfire batteries. See to it!
So we are to keep a low profile? I suppose that makes sense.
Do not trust these streets. Wealth is no measure of honesty.
My determination is equal to this task.
Someone else deal with this... skull.
Shepherding this servo-skull does not fall within my remit.
Daylight. Excellent! There are fewer shadows to hide the scofflaws!
This colony is not in optimum condition. Be prepared for a protracted extraction.
The battle lines have stalled. This is not a good sign.
To think, Tertium's water flows from this ... mire.
I do not care for the look of that atmospheric shield.
Many approaches. Many exits. Proceed with caution.
Tertium is subject to much decay. This is the consequence of straying from the Lex.
It is coming for you! Move!
With me! We will slay this abomination.
This fight will test us, but we will prevail!
Fight, for Atoma and the Lex!
I am watching you all, rejects!
Aid me, in the name of the Lex!
Aid me! Or face my judgement!
This place is unclean, like its residents.
Foul. None of you touch anything.
How the Atomans live in this filth, I do not know.
The corpse of this city reeks of decay.
Throne and damnation, they have me pinned!
Judge of Terra keep you, Lexmate!
May the Judge of Terra keep you, Behemoth.
Your death will not stand unavenged, Behemoth.
They were a liability. But they were OUR Liability!
You're with the Judge of Terra now, Firebrand.
Direct your attack at the weak points!
That armour is too thick. Aim elsewhere!
You cannot pierce that armour! Aim where it is weak!
Wasted effort. That armour is too thick!
The Judge of Terra grants us concealment.
Excellent. Nobody will expect the Arbitrator.
A residential area. Attempt to keep purging noise minimal.
Worker habs. High population density, high risk of trouble.
Finally, something useful. A weapons factory.
Had Atoma made more use of this place, perhaps she'd still be free.
Gun oil and gears keep the Imperium running.
A zone free of interest, free of crime.
A relief, when there is nothing and no one breaking the lex.
From my recollection of the map, this is Sector Periferus.
Please, I am trying to focus.
The Judge of Terra will have more interest in your predicament than I.
Your wound is not as bad as it looks.
You cannot fight on like this, lexmate.
A worthy kill! Atoma will be clear in no time!
Someone get them on their feet!
We'll have to be quick! They're going to fall!
Watch how it is done, Lexmate!
I have much to teach, if you are prepared to learn!
I am not without some small ability!
You are a true servant of the Lex.
I knew you would not fail me, Lexmate
I am much in your debt, Lexmate
Is this duty too much for you?
You are the master of your own fate!
The faster you attend to your wounds, the faster you can stop whining.
The Scholam instils fortitude. Something you're seemingly unaware of...
Significant blood loss. Do you require decommissioning?
If you're beyond salvage, please expire more efficiently.
That's easily fixable. See to it.
Malingering is a behavioural infraction. Heal, quickly.
If you wish to live, then heal.
With this error I also wound myself! Figuratively.
A lapse in attention on my part. Apologies.
Regrettably, you make a large target.
It is against protocol to obstruct an Arbitrator's duty.
Liability by name, Liability by nature.
If you were not blocking my line of sight, it would not have happened!
It's called fire protocol, Conscript. Ever heard of it?
I'll be noting your obstructiveness in my report.
The time of battle has come.
Think of this as a teachable moment.
I relish the opportunity to demonstrate correct combat tactics.
Take care, Behemoth. That looks nasty.
That's more than a scratch Behemoth.
Get that beast off the Ogryn!
Behemoth! Someone see to that Hound!
Hold on a little longer, Behemoth!
Hold fast for back up, Behemoth!
The Behemoth lays low our enemy!
You're showing the rest of us up, Behemoth!
I am rather gratified by that.
I am delighted to set an example.
I am grateful, Behemoth. Surprised, but grateful.
The Judge of Terra is with you!
The Judge of Terra hears your prayer!
Further complaints won't expedite your rescue.
You're bleeding. Do something about it.
You're even more of a liability when wounded.
Get the hound off the psyker!
Kill that hound, before it kills the liability!
Perhaps you are not a total Liability after all.
Get the psyker out of there.
It is how I was trained.
I am fast AND deadly, see?
Your help will not go unrewarded, Liability.
Try and call for help a litte more quietly, Conscript.
A professional knows better than to keep bleeding.
Look sharp, Conscript. You need Medicae.
The Pox Hound has the Conscript!
What are you doing down there?
You are supposed to be laying down the Lex, not yourself.
You've two feet, soldier. Use them!
Conscript! This isn't the time for hanging around.
This is how it is done.
I fight as I was trained.
This is how the Lex is served.
I take no pride in this.
I am in your debt, Conscript.
You have saved my life, Conscript.
I'll assist when I can, Firebrand.
May the Judge of Terra give you strength!
Show them the Judge of Terra's wrath!
Firebrand! What are you doing on that ledge?
Firebrand! There is no time for this!
Pride cometh before the fall, Firebrand.
I judge my performance as adequate.
The machine is corrupted. Like everything in this place.
Courage! A Beast of Nurgle comes!
Tread with care. That is a daemonhost.
We are adamant! They shall not prevail!
Stand your ground! Judge them all!
The fight is upon us! Show no fear!
We fight to the end! Do you hear me?
Not one step back! They shall all be judged!
Call your targets! Do not waste your shots!
They think that cover will save them!
Into the teeth of the fray!
Judge of Terra, they are dug in!
We are enfiladed! Close and kill!
Enemy in cover! Begin close assault!
The Lex demands your death, Shotgunner!
We need not fight these Poxwalkers.
By the Throne, we are surrounded!
Judge on Terra, they are everywhere!
The Lexbreakers are all around us!
No safe vector. Enemies are swarming!
Cover one another! Work as a team!
We have their measure. And the Judge of Terra's blessing!
We are adamant! We are immovable!
They shall find no victory here!
I do not care for this place.
This place. Lifeless. Abandoned by the Lex.
Move with care. This place is a haven for the scofflaw and the criminal.
A temple to industry. Fallen, of course.
If this place could be restored, what weapons it would make...
The locals have fled, I see.
Keep your eyes open. This may not be as empty as it appears.
Do the trains still run, here?
This zone is a mere ruin.
This place has been torn apart by war.
Clearly crime does not pay in these parts.
[Cough] Even the air here is corrupt.
Do you feel you have something to prove, Lexmate?
Pace yourself, Lexmate. This road is long.
The Ogryn is setting a fine example!
Watch the Ogryn. Now that's killing!
The Psyker may yet be of some use!
Liability? Not today! Today you are the Lex's hand!
I never thought I'd say this, but we can learn from that Psyker!
The Psyker might actually be competent!
You deliver judgement as one born to it, Veteran!
Your efforts are making me look bad, Conscript.
You are a master of death, Conscript.
Mad staring eyes and a body count. You truly are a Zealot.
Rage all you want, Zealot. I cannot argue with results!
